item.title: Stray cats - Stray Cat Strut
item.description:

Ooh— ooh—
ooh— ooh—
Black and orange stray
cat sitting on a fence
Ain’t got enough
dough to pay the rent
I’m flat broke
but I don’t care
I strut right by
with my tail
In the air
stray cat strut
I’m a ladies cat
I’m a feline casanova
Hey man that’s
that get a shoe
Thrown at me by
a mean old man
Get my dinner
from a garbage can-

I don’t bother
chasing mice around
Oh no I slink
down the alley
Looking for a fight
howling to the moon
On a hot summer night
singing the blues
While the lady
cats cry
Wild stray cat
you’re a real gone guy
I wish I could be
as carefree and wild
But I got cat class
and I got cat style-
